This paper deals with the security of obfuscated keys against invasive readout, which is a common topic in the computer security field (cs.CR). The methodology proposed in the paper involves the use of error correcting codes, which is a technique commonly used in software engineering (cs.SE) and electronic engineering (cs.ET). The paper also discusses the use of look-alike cells, which is a technique used in hardware design (cs.AR). Finally, the paper presents analysis and cost metrics, which are topics commonly discussed in machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG).
